WEBVTT

00:00.960 --> 00:02.463
-Where's that go?
-[Ben] Basement.

00:02.547 --> 00:03.925
You know what happened down there, right?

00:04.008 --> 00:05.469
[screaming]

00:06.429 --> 00:08.391
[gasping]

00:08.475 --> 00:12.734
-[Bratt] Son of a bitch!
-[suspenseful theme playing]

00:12.817 --> 00:15.865
[Harold]
Previously on Goosebumps...

00:15.949 --> 00:20.082
[Coach Rifkin]
Let's give it up for Isaiah Powers!

00:20.165 --> 00:21.459
[crowd cheering]

00:21.544 --> 00:22.754
I love you all so much.

00:22.837 --> 00:25.467
-Please don't drop the mic.
-[crowd cheering]

00:25.552 --> 00:29.141
That troll sent
the invite to my parents.

00:29.225 --> 00:30.561
I'm gonna have to
cancel the party.

00:30.645 --> 00:31.981
We just need a new venue.

00:34.360 --> 00:36.281
[partygoers chattering]

00:37.534 --> 00:39.287
[Isaiah] It's just a mask.

00:39.370 --> 00:40.581
-[camera clicking]
-[girls gasping]

00:40.665 --> 00:41.959
Say cheese!

00:42.544 --> 00:43.754
[Margot]
Hey, hey, is something wrong?

00:43.838 --> 00:45.758
Yeah. I could just really
use your help with this.

00:45.842 --> 00:47.554
-I know how crazy it sounds.
-I thought you were actually coming

00:47.637 --> 00:48.639
to check up on me.

00:48.723 --> 00:50.810
You're gonna have to solve
this one on your own.

00:50.893 --> 00:51.895
Stop the game.
Somebody, please!

00:51.979 --> 00:53.148
-Stop the game!
-[Lucas] Mom! Mom.

00:53.231 --> 00:54.233
[shouting]

00:58.784 --> 00:59.953
[Ben]
Nora, what are you doing here?

01:00.037 --> 01:01.582
I saw Biddle. He's come back

01:01.665 --> 01:04.086
to make us pay for what we did to him.

01:04.170 --> 01:05.506
[suspenseful theme playing]

01:26.130 --> 01:28.844
[alarm ringing and vibrating]

01:39.448 --> 01:42.329
["Nameless, Faceless"
by Courtney Barnett playing]

01:43.666 --> 01:45.377
♪ Don't you have anything ♪

01:45.460 --> 01:50.387
[Isabella speaking]

01:52.433 --> 01:56.567
[Isabella speaking]

01:57.192 --> 01:58.236
Izzy.

01:59.238 --> 02:00.908
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

02:00.992 --> 02:02.829
♪ At home in the darkness ♪

02:02.912 --> 02:05.960
♪ With all the pent-up rage
That you harness ♪

02:06.043 --> 02:07.421
-Thanks.
-You're welcome.

02:07.505 --> 02:08.841
♪ I'm real sorry ♪

02:08.924 --> 02:09.968
[girl 1 speaking]

02:10.051 --> 02:11.387
[girl 2 speaking]

02:11.471 --> 02:12.557
[boy speaking]

02:15.061 --> 02:16.690
[school bell rings]

02:16.773 --> 02:17.901
[James]
Dude, it's no all padding!

02:17.984 --> 02:19.403
There is real muscle under here.

02:19.487 --> 02:21.157
Yo, okay, so then
I was looking at her

02:21.240 --> 02:22.619
and I was like,

02:22.702 --> 02:23.871
"You should see
the other mascot."

02:23.954 --> 02:26.250
[laughter]

02:26.334 --> 02:27.712
[Coach Rifkin]
Look, Isaiah, Friday,

02:27.796 --> 02:29.841
there's gonna be a college scout
in the stands.

02:29.925 --> 02:31.512
This can't just be a good game.

02:31.595 --> 02:34.266
It's gotta be
your best game ever. Hmm?

02:34.350 --> 02:36.145
-Okay. Thank you.
-Hey, Coach.

02:36.229 --> 02:37.272
Okay, Titans!

02:37.356 --> 02:38.859
Beast mode!

02:38.943 --> 02:41.782
-Uh, Coach Rifkin.
-[Rifkin] Did I say that right?

02:41.865 --> 02:44.328
Coach? I have
the footage you asked for.

02:44.411 --> 02:45.413
Hey, Jack!

02:45.497 --> 02:47.000
[Jack] What's up, Coach?

02:47.084 --> 02:48.378
No, yeah, it can wait.

02:51.217 --> 02:53.514
So, Mom's not coming home
from Seattle this weekend?

02:53.597 --> 02:55.267
It's her birthday.

02:55.350 --> 02:57.145
Oh, honey, I'm sure
she feels terrible.

02:57.229 --> 02:59.985
Maybe she's got a big
photo shoot or something.

03:00.068 --> 03:01.822
[Margot] Why doesn't
she want to spend her birthday

03:01.905 --> 03:04.786
with her daughter and her
husband like a normal mom?

03:04.869 --> 03:07.207
[Colin]
You'll have to ask her, honey.

03:07.291 --> 03:09.295
Yeah, like she'd
tell me anything.

03:09.963 --> 03:11.675
Margot, are you okay?

03:11.758 --> 03:15.683
♪ You're just kidding ♪

03:15.766 --> 03:19.398
♪ He said, she said ♪

03:19.481 --> 03:21.987
♪ Nameless, faceless ♪

03:25.410 --> 03:28.041
[skateboard clattering]

03:28.959 --> 03:30.170
[Isabella grunts]

03:30.253 --> 03:32.132
[Lucas]
Oh, what's up, man?

03:32.634 --> 03:34.804
Lucas, are you insane?
You almost just killed me!

03:34.888 --> 03:36.516
Oh, sorry, I didn't see you.

03:38.854 --> 03:40.775
[school bell rings]

03:45.033 --> 03:47.245
[Isabella chuckles]
Jesus wants his hair back.

03:47.329 --> 03:48.916
[boy] Uh, no one asked.

03:48.999 --> 03:51.546
[Isabella] Daddy pay for
the lips or just the nose?

03:51.630 --> 03:53.383
[girl] So freaking rude.

03:54.511 --> 03:56.973
[Isabella] Nice shirt, does it
come in your size?

03:57.057 --> 03:59.019
You suck so hard, you blow.

03:59.103 --> 04:01.315
[overlapping chatter]

04:01.399 --> 04:02.401
Excuse you, clumsy.

04:02.484 --> 04:04.029
Sorry, Allison, I...

04:04.113 --> 04:05.448
That was my bad.

04:05.533 --> 04:07.787
So, what time does the party start?

04:07.870 --> 04:09.081
Eight.

04:09.164 --> 04:10.793
[Wendy]
And what time does it end?

04:10.876 --> 04:12.672
Sunrise, 'cause that's when my parents

04:12.755 --> 04:14.592
get back from upstate.

04:14.676 --> 04:15.678
Oh, yeah!

04:17.890 --> 04:20.395
-[phone clicking]
-[indistinct chatter]

04:20.478 --> 04:23.569
That stupid troll leaked
my invite to my parents.

04:23.652 --> 04:25.948
Texted, emailed and DM'd them.

04:26.032 --> 04:28.662
-Word?
-Who does that?

04:28.746 --> 04:31.543
Who hates me that much?

04:31.626 --> 04:33.839
My mom said I have to cancel the party.

04:33.922 --> 04:37.555
No, you don't.
You just need a new venue.

04:37.638 --> 04:38.724
Come on.

04:40.770 --> 04:42.189
[suspenseful theme playing]

04:47.199 --> 04:48.911
Izzy!

04:48.994 --> 04:50.371
Look what I found.

04:52.585 --> 04:55.841
Your old vampiress costume.

04:55.925 --> 04:58.597
Why would I go to a party
I tried to sabotage?

04:58.680 --> 05:01.060
You tried and failed.

05:01.143 --> 05:02.814
I say it's fate.

05:02.897 --> 05:04.526
Besides, don't you want to see

05:04.609 --> 05:06.780
the Biddle death house in person?

05:06.863 --> 05:08.491
Not my thing.

05:08.575 --> 05:11.748
Plus, I was like 12
when I last wore that.

05:11.832 --> 05:12.834
So?

05:12.917 --> 05:14.378
Vampires never go out of style.

05:15.421 --> 05:19.137
They... literally can't.
[chuckles]

05:19.221 --> 05:21.893
'Cause they live forever.
'Cause they're vampires.

05:21.977 --> 05:23.897
You have to stop
explaining your jokes.

05:23.981 --> 05:26.110
Whatever. You should go, 'cause
you're anxious and miserable,

05:26.193 --> 05:27.738
and a party would make you happy.

05:27.822 --> 05:29.701
-I can't.
-[Alan] Why?

05:29.784 --> 05:31.788
Because nobody knows me at school.

05:31.872 --> 05:33.667
I am literally invisible to them.

05:34.293 --> 05:36.213
Maybe that's 'cause
you never even join in.

05:37.424 --> 05:38.927
What's the worst that could happen?

05:40.931 --> 05:42.768
[in high-pitched voice]
Wear me, Isabella.

05:44.981 --> 05:47.570
[upbeat pop music playing
over speakers in distance]

06:07.568 --> 06:09.530
[girls giggling]

06:09.614 --> 06:11.325
-[Allison] Oh, my gosh!
-[giggling]

06:19.007 --> 06:20.260
[sighs]

06:27.984 --> 06:29.152
[Mask] Isabella?

06:30.906 --> 06:32.367
[suspenseful theme playing]

06:40.801 --> 06:42.930
Hello? Is someone there?

06:44.266 --> 06:45.936
[door creaking]

06:51.030 --> 06:52.992
[Mask] Isabella.

06:53.075 --> 06:54.244
Hello?

07:25.098 --> 07:26.518
Isabella.

07:30.776 --> 07:31.778
Isabella.

07:38.124 --> 07:42.842
You deserve to be seen. Just put me on.

07:59.124 --> 08:01.461
[mysterious theme playing]

08:19.497 --> 08:20.542
[door creaking]

08:24.466 --> 08:28.432
["It Girl by Kah-Lo" by Karma
Fields & Associanu playing]

08:28.516 --> 08:30.938
♪ Let me tell you a story
About a girl ♪

08:32.983 --> 08:35.279
♪ She walked around
Like she ran the world ♪

08:37.283 --> 08:40.081
♪ She walked around
Like she knew everything ♪

08:41.793 --> 08:44.047
♪ And wouldn't back down
'Til you kiss her ring ♪

08:46.009 --> 08:49.057
♪ She had that certain
Je ne sais quoi ♪

08:49.809 --> 08:54.150
♪ That girl is a dream ♪

08:54.234 --> 08:58.450
♪ She means everything ♪

08:58.535 --> 09:03.043
♪ That girl is a dream ♪

09:03.127 --> 09:05.924
♪ She means everything ♪

09:06.008 --> 09:08.387
♪ She has "it" ♪

09:15.861 --> 09:19.409
Oh, my God, oh, my God.
Oh, my God, that party was wild!

09:19.910 --> 09:21.204
[exhales sharply]

09:27.342 --> 09:29.680
[suspenseful theme playing]

09:29.764 --> 09:31.391
[fabric holding]

09:32.185 --> 09:33.270
[grunts]

09:39.617 --> 09:41.495
[gasps, panting]

09:46.254 --> 09:47.716
[laughing]

10:08.925 --> 10:10.302
[loud roaring]

10:13.392 --> 10:16.481
[slow mysterious theme playing]

10:17.901 --> 10:19.237
[line ringing]

10:19.320 --> 10:20.574
[James on voicemail]
Hey, it's James.

10:20.657 --> 10:21.951
Leave a message.

10:22.034 --> 10:23.538
-[message prompt beeps]
-James, it's me.

10:23.621 --> 10:25.374
I really need to talk to you, okay?

10:26.753 --> 10:30.259
[sighs] I can't believe you're
making me leave you a voicemail.

10:30.342 --> 10:32.973
Can you call me? Please?

10:33.056 --> 10:34.309
Thanks.

10:35.770 --> 10:38.066
-[Margot] Hey.
-[Isaiah] Oh, hey.

10:38.150 --> 10:39.570
I'm not bothering you, am I?

10:39.653 --> 10:40.739
-No, no, no.
-Okay.

10:40.822 --> 10:42.492
No, you're all good.

10:42.576 --> 10:44.622
You're all good, I'm just...

10:44.705 --> 10:46.500
-sorting some stuff out.
-Hey, hey.

10:46.584 --> 10:48.086
What... I got it.

10:48.170 --> 10:50.382
-You have a broken arm.
-Oh, really?

10:50.466 --> 10:52.094
I didn't notice.

10:52.888 --> 10:55.602
Okay, I'm sorry. That was me
expressing empathy badly.

10:55.685 --> 10:57.564
No. No, no, no.

10:57.648 --> 10:59.108
You're not,
you're not bad at it.

10:59.192 --> 11:02.156
It's just everything sucks right now.

11:02.240 --> 11:03.785
So...

11:03.868 --> 11:07.124
Oh, please, take a seat at...
at my bakery.

11:07.208 --> 11:09.797
[giggling] Every cookie
in Port Lawrence.

11:09.880 --> 11:11.634
Yeah, every five minutes
someone shows up

11:11.717 --> 11:13.262
with a new baked good.

11:13.345 --> 11:16.393
So, what happens now?

11:18.063 --> 11:19.567
Rehab.

11:19.650 --> 11:23.115
They're saying I got
like six months minimum.

11:23.198 --> 11:24.242
So...

11:26.121 --> 11:28.208
So my scholarship's up
in the air right now.

11:29.878 --> 11:35.139
Look, Isaiah, I'm really
sorry about the other day.

11:35.222 --> 11:38.437
You were in trouble and I just,
I threw it back in your face.

11:39.898 --> 11:41.401
Do you want any of this mess?

11:42.946 --> 11:46.579
I'm sure one of these
does not contain nuts.

11:46.662 --> 11:49.334
Isaiah, what you told me
about the camera.

11:49.417 --> 11:51.421
Look, I saw it. I saw it happen.

11:51.505 --> 11:52.758
Okay, all of these contain nuts.

11:52.841 --> 11:55.012
Literally, any of these will kill you.

11:55.095 --> 11:56.097
It makes no sense.

11:56.181 --> 11:57.851
Why would you put nuts
in all baked goods?

11:57.934 --> 12:00.272
It's like putting avocado in a BLT.

12:00.356 --> 12:02.611
It's just a way of ruining
a perfectly good thing.

12:02.694 --> 12:06.117
Isaiah, I saw you on the field

12:06.201 --> 12:07.996
and something was clearly wrong.

12:11.211 --> 12:13.508
What did you see out there
before you broke your arm?

12:15.637 --> 12:17.933
You're better off staying
far away from this.

12:20.145 --> 12:21.524
Far away from what?

12:23.485 --> 12:25.322
I need to get back to all this.

12:25.406 --> 12:27.118
Thank you for coming round.

12:29.038 --> 12:30.457
Bye.

12:30.542 --> 12:33.046
[door opens, closes]

12:40.144 --> 12:41.438
[Mask] Wait.

12:41.939 --> 12:43.776
[suspenseful theme playing]

13:20.809 --> 13:22.436
[groaning]

13:38.803 --> 13:39.888
[groans]

13:40.890 --> 13:42.351
Oh, man.

13:46.986 --> 13:48.363
I'm a lightweight.

13:50.158 --> 13:52.539
Oh, boy.

13:53.791 --> 13:55.002
Whew!

13:56.672 --> 13:59.427
Okay, back on track.

14:03.561 --> 14:05.690
[suspenseful theme playing]

14:13.079 --> 14:15.000
[panting]

14:17.547 --> 14:18.674
Ow.

14:25.354 --> 14:26.982
Monday?

14:27.066 --> 14:28.318
Monday!

14:28.401 --> 14:29.613
Oh, God!

14:29.696 --> 14:30.990
Oh, shoot!

14:34.873 --> 14:36.209
What the hell?

14:47.189 --> 14:48.358
[whispering] Okay.

14:52.074 --> 14:53.536
Heh. Just slipped.

14:54.161 --> 14:55.790
[loud banging]

14:59.756 --> 15:00.800
Hey, you guys.

15:02.094 --> 15:03.179
Go Titans.

15:16.665 --> 15:18.001
[grunting]

15:21.550 --> 15:22.886
Hey, hey, Teresa.

15:27.269 --> 15:28.313
Oh, God.

15:29.733 --> 15:31.110
[grunting]

15:32.112 --> 15:33.198
Dropped my glasses.

15:35.285 --> 15:36.287
[panting]

15:36.370 --> 15:38.291
[male student] Mr. Bratt,
uh, are you okay?

15:38.374 --> 15:40.462
It was something I ate.
[chuckles]

15:40.546 --> 15:41.799
Bathroom.

15:46.975 --> 15:48.938
Oh, God! Okay.

15:49.021 --> 15:50.190
[panting]

15:50.273 --> 15:52.194
Oh, my God. What's happening?

15:52.277 --> 15:54.115
Oh, my God.

15:54.198 --> 15:55.827
-[tense theme playing]
-[screams]

15:56.662 --> 15:58.456
Okay. Okay.

15:59.876 --> 16:01.337
[chuckling]

16:01.420 --> 16:02.966
You're not real.

16:03.049 --> 16:05.095
Help me find him.

16:05.178 --> 16:07.015
You leave me alone!

16:08.309 --> 16:10.147
Everything's gonna be fine.

16:17.452 --> 16:18.831
Please.

16:29.101 --> 16:30.855
-[whistle blows]
-[players grunting]

16:34.445 --> 16:37.619
-[drone humming]
-[whistle blows]

16:43.589 --> 16:45.760
[indistinct chatter]

16:47.972 --> 16:51.020
-[Isaiah] Hey, Susan.
-Hey.

16:52.607 --> 16:54.401
You get footage of all the games, right?

16:55.362 --> 16:56.615
I do.

16:57.575 --> 16:58.911
Well, can you give me Friday's?

17:00.790 --> 17:02.543
-You mean when you...
-Yeah.

17:05.006 --> 17:06.802
Are you sure you wanna see that?

17:06.885 --> 17:09.098
Well, you watch film to learn
from your mistakes, right?

17:09.891 --> 17:11.143
Yeah. Okay.

17:11.227 --> 17:14.985
Um, it's on my A.V. cart.

17:16.404 --> 17:18.784
-Can you watch the drone?
-Yeah, sure.

17:18.867 --> 17:20.328
Okay, just...

17:24.044 --> 17:25.088
Hmm.

17:26.675 --> 17:28.637
Hey, so, um...

17:28.721 --> 17:31.225
how long have you been
doing this A.V. Club thing?

17:31.309 --> 17:33.939
Don't touch that. Freshman year.

17:36.152 --> 17:39.325
Damn, that's a long time.

17:40.368 --> 17:42.331
Hey, you know what's weird?

17:42.414 --> 17:44.753
We've been in school together for years,

17:44.836 --> 17:47.382
but like I know nothing about you.

17:47.466 --> 17:48.719
[Isabella scoffs]

17:48.802 --> 17:50.221
Including my name,

17:50.765 --> 17:54.856
which is not Susan, by the way.

17:54.939 --> 17:57.319
It's Isabella.

17:57.402 --> 17:59.574
-For real?
-For real.

18:00.408 --> 18:04.166
Damn. Hey, I'm sorry.

18:04.249 --> 18:05.836
I didn't mean...

18:05.920 --> 18:07.255
It's fine.

18:07.339 --> 18:08.926
Uh, start, stop.

18:09.009 --> 18:10.763
[Isaiah] Mm-hmm...

18:10.846 --> 18:12.015
Do you need me to stay or...

18:12.099 --> 18:13.267
Uh, no.

18:13.351 --> 18:14.938
I can take it from here, Susan.

18:16.190 --> 18:17.527
No problem, Isaac.

18:20.073 --> 18:21.827
[Isaiah] Nice.

18:21.910 --> 18:22.912
Hey.

18:24.248 --> 18:25.710
Thank you, Isabella.

18:26.962 --> 18:28.297
I really appreciate this.

18:29.425 --> 18:30.678
Yeah.

18:32.723 --> 18:34.435
[cheering and shouting on video]

18:37.274 --> 18:38.861
-[whistle blows]
-[crowd groans]

18:42.785 --> 18:44.371
[drone humming]

18:47.419 --> 18:50.300
Lucas, what the hell
are you doing?

18:50.383 --> 18:51.385
[laughing]

18:51.469 --> 18:52.680
[Isabella]
Please, I'm begging you, do not.

18:52.763 --> 18:54.851
-Do it!
-[male student] Get it, dude!

18:55.686 --> 18:56.730
No!

19:01.030 --> 19:03.034
I'm sorry, Mr. Stokes.
I'm never going to hang

19:03.117 --> 19:06.332
from a stolen drone
ever again, okay?

19:06.415 --> 19:09.421
You don't need to apologize
to me. It's not my drone.

19:11.676 --> 19:13.471
Look, I'm really sorry.

19:14.849 --> 19:16.978
In my defense,
I didn't know it was yours.

19:17.522 --> 19:18.982
I thought it was
like school property,

19:19.066 --> 19:21.237
which is like a little
different, you know?

19:21.320 --> 19:23.199
And in my brain I was
sort of thinking about

19:23.282 --> 19:25.328
like robots
taking over the world

19:25.411 --> 19:27.249
and... [stutters]
that seems to be...

19:27.332 --> 19:29.002
[mysterious theme playing]

19:29.086 --> 19:31.215
[Mask] You know
he doesn't mean it.

19:32.718 --> 19:33.971
He's a liar.

19:34.471 --> 19:36.475
You know, if there is
a silver lining to any of this,

19:36.560 --> 19:38.897
it's that, you know,
humanity isn't doomed.

19:39.481 --> 19:40.483
[Isabella] Uh-huh.

19:41.778 --> 19:43.114
Thank you so much for fighting

19:43.197 --> 19:44.701
the robots for us, Lucas,

19:44.784 --> 19:46.746
but I think you're going to
have to do more than apologize.

19:46.830 --> 19:49.627
I think you're gonna have
to make good financially.

19:49.711 --> 19:52.173
Uh, yeah, I can do
like five bucks a week

19:52.257 --> 19:53.927
till it's paid for.

19:54.011 --> 19:57.309
-[scoffs]
-Okay, I mean that's an offer.

19:57.392 --> 19:59.772
Is that something that
both parties can agree to?

19:59.856 --> 20:01.108
[Mask] No.

20:02.820 --> 20:04.239
Yeah, sure.

20:04.323 --> 20:05.910
Okay, yeah, great.

20:06.828 --> 20:09.333
[Mask] Do not back down.

20:10.293 --> 20:11.880
You know what, no.

20:11.963 --> 20:14.927
This drone cost $3,000.

20:15.011 --> 20:17.767
And if this moron
somehow manages to graduate,

20:17.850 --> 20:19.478
he will never make that money back

20:19.562 --> 20:21.440
flipping burgers for the rest of his life.

20:21.524 --> 20:23.486
[scoffs]
Why is this chick like so intense?

20:23.570 --> 20:25.073
Okay, I don't think she meant that.

20:25.156 --> 20:26.701
I think tempers are
just running hot right now.

20:26.785 --> 20:30.458
Oh, no. No, this chick
did mean all of that.

20:30.542 --> 20:32.170
I'm just telling Lucas to his face

20:32.253 --> 20:33.715
what everyone says behind his back.

20:33.799 --> 20:38.809
Which is that you are a pathetic person.

20:38.892 --> 20:42.650
This, this whole Jackass facade
is honestly sad.

20:42.733 --> 20:46.908
Whoa, whoa, okay, let's just
try to take it down a notch.

20:46.991 --> 20:49.329
Mmm. Well, how's this?

20:49.413 --> 20:51.458
You're a high school
guidance counselor.

20:51.543 --> 20:54.381
-You literally failed at life.
-Dude.

20:54.464 --> 20:56.301
I'm here because
I love helping kids.

20:56.385 --> 20:59.182
Here's the thing, Colin.
You didn't help me.

20:59.266 --> 21:01.563
You made my life
a whole lot worse,

21:01.646 --> 21:03.023
'cause now my mom
is gonna kill me.

21:03.107 --> 21:04.902
And I mean, kill me.

21:04.986 --> 21:06.906
And it's because
you're an idiot,

21:06.990 --> 21:09.327
and you're worse than an idiot.

21:10.038 --> 21:11.039
You're weak.

21:18.179 --> 21:19.181
Sorry.

21:20.517 --> 21:21.895
I'm so sorry.

21:23.063 --> 21:24.316
Sorry.

21:27.948 --> 21:29.619
Um, forget what I said.

21:29.702 --> 21:30.871
The money thing is fine.

21:30.954 --> 21:32.290
Five bucks a week.

21:33.125 --> 21:34.712
Sorry.

21:37.467 --> 21:38.887
[sighs]

21:39.471 --> 21:44.481
So, is that settled?

21:44.565 --> 21:46.528
Yeah, please go to detention.

21:47.738 --> 21:49.115
-For the record I think you're--
-It's okay.

21:49.199 --> 21:50.619
You can just go to detention.

22:00.388 --> 22:02.350
-[suspenseful theme playing]
-[distant players shouting]

22:07.235 --> 22:08.237
That's right!

22:08.320 --> 22:09.699
[Coach Rifkin]
We still got another half!

22:09.782 --> 22:11.703
Get out there
and keep up the intensity

22:11.786 --> 22:13.122
and finish strong!

22:13.205 --> 22:14.667
[muffled shouting]

22:32.953 --> 22:34.039
[whistle blows]

22:34.122 --> 22:35.792
[laughs]

22:36.293 --> 22:37.963
Sorry, I don't mean
to scare you like that.

22:38.047 --> 22:41.178
-You made me jump, sir.
-I'm practicing to be a ref.

22:41.261 --> 22:43.642
-I guess the whistle works.
-It sure does.

22:43.725 --> 22:45.311
Oh, I got it, I got it.

22:45.394 --> 22:47.816
-Thanks.
-Sure.

22:47.900 --> 22:50.238
Hey, you know, your dad,

22:50.321 --> 22:52.200
-he did some work on my house.
-Okay.

22:52.283 --> 22:54.329
He used to play football
here too, right?

22:55.039 --> 22:58.212
Yeah, he did.
Um, how did you know?

22:59.255 --> 23:00.926
I know a lot about my students.

23:03.556 --> 23:04.934
I gotta get back to class.

23:07.355 --> 23:08.775
Sorry about the arm.

23:08.858 --> 23:11.279
-That's not your fault.
-I know.

23:11.363 --> 23:12.741
[both chuckle]

23:12.825 --> 23:14.244
Can you imagine?

23:19.045 --> 23:20.590
-Okay.
-Okay.

23:21.174 --> 23:22.845
-Okay.
-Okay.

23:22.928 --> 23:25.349
Good luck with
the ref situation.

23:25.433 --> 23:27.186
-[whistle blows]
-Get to class.

23:27.270 --> 23:28.690
-[both laughing]
-I will do.

23:28.773 --> 23:29.817
-[chuckles]
-[Isaiah] Thank you.

23:33.449 --> 23:35.411
[gentle theme playing]

23:35.494 --> 23:37.206
Got you some coffee.

23:37.290 --> 23:38.710
But then I realized
that was dumb.

23:38.793 --> 23:40.254
You work in a coffee shop,

23:40.338 --> 23:42.383
but I didn't want
to come empty handed, so...

23:43.511 --> 23:45.473
No, uh, I can use

23:45.557 --> 23:47.143
all the coffee I can get today.

23:47.226 --> 23:50.024
Oh, is now not a good time?

23:50.107 --> 23:52.445
No, it's, it's fine. I just, uh,

23:52.529 --> 23:54.449
I just thought I was seeing you tonight.

23:54.533 --> 23:56.119
-Yeah.
-You're not canceling, are you?

23:56.203 --> 23:59.794
No. But this is actually about Lucas.

23:59.877 --> 24:02.674
Oh, no. What did he do now?

24:02.758 --> 24:04.094
Well, um...

24:07.518 --> 24:11.066
He kind of destroyed Isabella Chen Lopez's
$3,000 drone.

24:11.149 --> 24:12.528
Oh, my God.

24:12.611 --> 24:13.863
I can't pay for that.

24:13.947 --> 24:15.617
Yeah, I'll talk to her parents

24:15.700 --> 24:16.911
and try to work something out.

24:16.994 --> 24:21.712
But, look, Lucas has got
to get his act together.

24:21.796 --> 24:24.885
You know, I don't want
this to affect his future.

24:24.969 --> 24:26.514
Yeah, no, I...

24:26.597 --> 24:28.100
You know, I knew when Dennis died,

24:28.183 --> 24:30.438
it was gonna be--
it was gonna be hard,

24:30.522 --> 24:34.070
but I, I thought he was gonna be sad.

24:34.154 --> 24:37.034
-Not reckless.
-Hey, come here.

24:38.580 --> 24:40.458
[Colin]
You're doing a great job with Lucas.

24:40.542 --> 24:43.297
It's just, you know, it's hard.

24:44.675 --> 24:46.094
-[door opens]
-[door chime jingling]

24:46.178 --> 24:49.935
Colin? Elsie, from the nursery.

24:50.019 --> 24:51.438
Yes.

24:51.522 --> 24:54.027
[Elsie] How's your wife?
Still gardening, I hope?

24:54.110 --> 24:56.323
My wife? Yeah, she's doing great, Elsie.

24:56.406 --> 24:58.870
Um, she's in Seattle for work,

24:58.953 --> 25:00.874
so the gardening has fallen to me,

25:00.957 --> 25:03.045
-unfortunately for the plants.
-[Elsie and Colin chuckle]

25:03.128 --> 25:05.341
-Well, tell her I said hi.
-Yeah, I will.

25:07.094 --> 25:08.263
Sorry.

25:09.182 --> 25:11.144
-I gotta get back in.
-[Colin] Oh.

25:12.396 --> 25:14.275
-See you tonight.
-Okay.

25:18.826 --> 25:20.914
It isn't my fault.

25:20.997 --> 25:22.876
Lucas Parker stole it.

25:22.960 --> 25:24.964
Did Lucas Parker borrow
the drone from your father

25:25.047 --> 25:26.717
without permission
and take it to school?

25:26.801 --> 25:28.805
No, but Dad isn't even around to ask.

25:28.888 --> 25:30.642
[Victoria] The drone was
in your care when it broke,

25:30.725 --> 25:32.563
so it's your responsibility.

25:32.646 --> 25:34.023
You're grounded.

25:34.107 --> 25:36.278
So I have to stay home? Fine.

25:36.361 --> 25:38.282
It's kind of par
for the course these days.

25:38.365 --> 25:40.160
Not just that.

25:40.244 --> 25:42.373
No phone, no Internet, no computer.

25:42.456 --> 25:44.127
Oh, that is not fair!

25:44.210 --> 25:45.880
How, how am I supposed
to do my homework?

25:45.964 --> 25:48.135
-Long hand.
-[scoffs]

25:48.218 --> 25:50.014
No wonder Dad doesn't wanna be around.

25:57.529 --> 25:59.992
[exclaims]

26:00.075 --> 26:01.662
["Terrible Lie"
by Nine Inch Nails playing]

26:01.746 --> 26:03.750
♪ Why are you doing this to me ♪

26:06.212 --> 26:11.056
♪ Am I not living up
To what I'm supposed to be ♪

26:11.139 --> 26:15.523
♪ Why am I seething
With this animosity ♪

26:15.607 --> 26:17.360
♪ Hey, God ♪

26:17.443 --> 26:21.284
♪ I think you owe me
A great big apology ♪

26:21.368 --> 26:23.831
[flames crackling]

26:23.915 --> 26:26.461
-[door chime jingles]
-Yes! I love this song.

26:26.545 --> 26:29.133
♪ Terrible lie ♪

26:29.217 --> 26:31.137
I-I'm sorry.
We're actually closing.

26:31.221 --> 26:33.016
We're not open for dinner.

26:33.100 --> 26:34.978
Oh, no!

26:36.732 --> 26:39.530
Shoot, I was really hoping
to jam on an egg sandwich.

26:43.161 --> 26:44.623
Um, okay.

26:44.707 --> 26:46.627
I'm sure I can
warm one of those up.

26:47.879 --> 26:48.965
Thank you.

26:49.465 --> 26:50.760
[Nora exclaims]

26:52.931 --> 26:54.518
-Okay...
-Could I have that one?

26:55.728 --> 26:58.024
Yeah. Have we met?

26:59.695 --> 27:01.364
No, I don't think so.

27:01.448 --> 27:03.160
I've never
been here before, so...

27:03.243 --> 27:07.168
Oh, wait, are you Mr. Bratt?

27:08.170 --> 27:10.090
Yes. Heh.

27:10.174 --> 27:11.552
Yes, I am.

27:11.635 --> 27:13.931
Nathan Bratt.
I'm the new English teacher.

27:15.058 --> 27:16.352
My son loves you.

27:16.436 --> 27:18.190
I mean, well, he said,

27:18.273 --> 27:19.693
"He's not the worst,"

27:19.776 --> 27:21.237
which is really
the highest compliment

27:21.321 --> 27:22.783
you can get from him these days.

27:22.866 --> 27:24.327
Okay.

27:25.705 --> 27:28.043
So do you live near here?

27:28.126 --> 27:30.673
Um, no, I live
on the edge of town.

27:31.550 --> 27:32.844
The old Biddle house.

27:36.100 --> 27:37.269
The Biddle house?

27:37.353 --> 27:38.648
How long have you lived there?

27:38.731 --> 27:40.067
Just been a few days.

27:41.402 --> 27:42.906
You know, I hear it's haunted,

27:42.989 --> 27:45.244
which, you know, I don't know,

27:45.327 --> 27:48.543
have you seen anything
strange happening there?

27:48.626 --> 27:51.130
No. Not that I can think of.

27:52.592 --> 27:54.470
I did hear the horrible story

27:54.555 --> 27:56.432
about the boy who used
to lived there, though.

27:56.517 --> 27:59.438
-Yes, Harold.
-[Bratt] Yeah.

28:01.192 --> 28:02.403
It was sad.

28:03.071 --> 28:04.448
Kids can be so cruel.

28:06.077 --> 28:07.246
What do you mean?

28:07.329 --> 28:09.000
Well, it's just that everyone

28:09.083 --> 28:12.423
seems to have forgotten
about him and moved on.

28:13.593 --> 28:14.886
Not everyone.

28:16.180 --> 28:18.561
[oven beeps]

28:25.950 --> 28:27.244
[Nora mutters]

28:37.222 --> 28:38.475
[tense theme playing]

28:40.354 --> 28:41.982
You shouldn't be back here.

28:42.066 --> 28:43.401
Says who?

28:43.485 --> 28:45.948
[chuckles] I'm just kidding.

28:46.032 --> 28:47.577
I wanted one of these.

28:49.413 --> 28:50.499
Cocoa.

28:51.250 --> 28:52.671
Okay. Oh.

28:53.338 --> 28:54.340
Thanks, Nora.

29:00.227 --> 29:02.607
Thanks, Mr. Bratt.

29:02.691 --> 29:04.569
[cashier keys clacking]

29:06.949 --> 29:08.368
[suspenseful theme playing]

29:19.641 --> 29:21.060
[sighs] All right...

29:23.524 --> 29:26.070
-Oh, hey, here. Here.
-Oh!

29:26.154 --> 29:27.364
-Let me...
-Hey, thanks, Nora.

29:28.324 --> 29:30.203
Uh, my dad's inside.

29:30.287 --> 29:33.168
Yeah, um, actually, I would,

29:33.251 --> 29:34.504
I'd love to talk to you.

29:34.588 --> 29:35.923
Okay.

29:36.675 --> 29:39.221
I just wanted to ask you
about the game.

29:39.305 --> 29:41.184
What about it?

29:41.267 --> 29:42.687
-Well...
-[Ben] Isaiah.

29:44.566 --> 29:45.568
Go inside.

29:50.494 --> 29:52.247
Yeah, okay. I'll see you later.

29:52.331 --> 29:55.253
-Okay, bye.
-[Ben] I'll be in in a minute.

29:55.337 --> 29:56.380
[Isaiah] Cool.

29:59.303 --> 30:01.558
I told you, I don't want
your dark creepy crap

30:01.642 --> 30:03.269
around my family.

30:03.353 --> 30:04.396
He's been through enough.

30:04.480 --> 30:06.359
Ben, just hear me out.

30:06.442 --> 30:08.614
About what? Biddle?

30:08.697 --> 30:11.035
His ghost broke my son's arm?
Is that what you're saying?

30:11.118 --> 30:13.582
I don't know what
I'm saying exactly, I just--

30:13.666 --> 30:15.001
Go home, Nora.

30:16.462 --> 30:17.799
This is getting sad.

30:17.882 --> 30:19.176
Ben...

30:19.803 --> 30:22.057
[Ben] I'm calling the others.
We need to talk.

30:30.407 --> 30:32.077
Hey, Margot.

30:33.079 --> 30:34.875
[Margot] Hey, Ms. Parker.

30:34.958 --> 30:37.254
-Can I talk to you for a sec?
-[Margot] Yeah, sure.

30:39.843 --> 30:41.805
-Hey, what's up?
-Hey, listen, um...

30:44.268 --> 30:45.521
Do me a favor.

30:46.272 --> 30:47.775
Give this photo to Isaiah.

30:48.527 --> 30:50.740
Ask him if he recognizes this kid.

30:50.823 --> 30:52.577
[suspenseful theme playing]

31:05.895 --> 31:07.815
[mysterious theme playing]

31:14.746 --> 31:15.873
[grunts in frustration]

31:20.256 --> 31:22.135
Izzy, check it out!

31:22.219 --> 31:23.471
[Isabella]
Not in the mood, dude.

31:23.555 --> 31:25.141
No, look, it's evidence.

31:26.394 --> 31:29.149
[Isabella on video]
Lucas! What the hell are you doing?

31:29.233 --> 31:31.070
-[Lucas chuckling on video]
-[Isabella] Are you kidding me?

31:31.153 --> 31:32.657
-He posted this?
-Uh-huh, yeah.

31:32.740 --> 31:35.120
And you can show Dad.
Show him it wasn't your fault.

31:35.203 --> 31:36.288
[clamoring]

31:36.372 --> 31:37.625
-[Lucas screaming]
-No.

31:37.709 --> 31:39.754
I will handle this.

31:39.838 --> 31:42.050
Oh-ho-ho, what are we gonna do?

31:42.134 --> 31:43.595
We are not going to do anything.

31:43.679 --> 31:45.223
-Huh?
-I will handle this.

31:45.306 --> 31:46.560
Wait, are we gonna do, a trap?

31:46.643 --> 31:48.021
I've always wanted to do a trap.

31:48.104 --> 31:49.273
No, no, leave me alone.

31:49.356 --> 31:50.526
[Alan] No, wait!

31:51.152 --> 31:52.154
Izzy!

31:52.237 --> 31:54.158
[Mask] Let me help you.

31:55.368 --> 31:57.039
-[knocks on door]
-[Alan] Izzy!

31:57.122 --> 31:58.917
Where did you get this?

31:59.669 --> 32:00.921
[Isabella] From Nora.

32:01.005 --> 32:03.092
Why, do you recognize him?

32:03.886 --> 32:06.432
Yeah. Yeah, I do.

32:09.188 --> 32:10.941
I saw him on the football field.

32:12.152 --> 32:13.989
He was the referee...

32:14.073 --> 32:15.618
and...

32:15.701 --> 32:17.120
and then he was on fire.

32:19.584 --> 32:20.669
Who is he?

32:22.172 --> 32:24.719
Well, I did some research,

32:24.803 --> 32:28.392
and I'm... I'm pretty sure
that's Harold Biddle.

32:28.476 --> 32:30.188
What, the kid that died in that house?

32:30.856 --> 32:32.025
Wait.

32:32.985 --> 32:35.699
Okay, I think we need to go
to Nora at the Harbor Stop.

32:35.783 --> 32:37.995
She clearly knows more
than she's letting on.

32:38.079 --> 32:39.164
[door chime jingles]

32:43.924 --> 32:46.428
[skateboard thumps, rolling away]

32:55.029 --> 32:56.198
[Lucas] Yes!

33:06.595 --> 33:07.680
Damn it.

33:14.234 --> 33:15.696
Hello?

33:15.779 --> 33:17.407
[suspenseful theme playing]

33:28.471 --> 33:29.473
Um...

33:31.352 --> 33:32.479
Can you not drag that?

33:32.563 --> 33:34.859
It's, um, expensive.

33:40.411 --> 33:41.623
[Lucas groans in pain]

33:46.800 --> 33:48.052
[grunting]

33:48.971 --> 33:50.098
[grunting]

33:55.651 --> 33:57.530
[grunting]

34:05.295 --> 34:07.925
[monstrous grunting]

34:16.901 --> 34:18.112
Move out!

34:18.989 --> 34:20.283
Get back!

34:24.291 --> 34:25.627
What the hell was that?

34:28.215 --> 34:29.677
Oh, my God, Lucas!

34:30.470 --> 34:31.973
[Margot]
Thank God we came here.

34:32.057 --> 34:33.977
-[Lucas groaning]
-Are you okay? Lucas.

34:35.313 --> 34:37.192
Yo, what just happened?

34:37.275 --> 34:39.697
[sighs] It's okay.

34:42.745 --> 34:45.166
[suspenseful theme playing]

34:51.470 --> 34:52.848
[suspenseful theme playing]

34:54.101 --> 34:56.523
[Victoria] Hi, honey,
I'm headed back to work,

34:56.606 --> 34:58.527
but I just wanted
to get your thoughts

34:58.610 --> 35:00.196
on how to deal with Isabella.

35:01.198 --> 35:04.287
Her attitude has been terrible lately.

35:09.423 --> 35:11.009
Something's gotten into her,

35:11.093 --> 35:13.724
and I could really use your support.

35:20.069 --> 35:21.155
Isabella?

35:22.825 --> 35:23.994
Alan?

35:26.624 --> 35:28.753
-Can I have a fruit gummy?
-[Victoria scoffs]

35:28.837 --> 35:30.674
That's just sugar.

35:30.757 --> 35:32.177
It's shaped like fruit.

35:33.513 --> 35:34.599
Have an apple.

35:34.682 --> 35:37.187
[Alan groans] Ew.

35:39.441 --> 35:40.694
I've been called in,

35:40.777 --> 35:42.656
but your sister
should be home any second.

35:55.682 --> 35:57.143
[thuds]

36:00.316 --> 36:05.159
[thumping]

36:18.687 --> 36:20.231
[glass shattering]

36:29.917 --> 36:31.044
-[grunts]
-[Alan gasps]

36:33.299 --> 36:35.929
-[loud grunting]
-[objects rustling]

36:52.713 --> 36:54.925
[phone beeps]

36:55.009 --> 36:57.263
[quietly] Please pick up,
please pick up, please pick up,

36:57.347 --> 36:59.100
-please pick up.
-[phone ringing]

37:00.729 --> 37:02.524
[ringing continues]

37:04.862 --> 37:06.198
Izzy?

37:08.410 --> 37:09.872
[screams]

37:14.674 --> 37:16.134
[intensifying theme playing]

37:16.218 --> 37:18.097
[sniffing]

37:27.365 --> 37:28.492
[door banging]

37:37.176 --> 37:39.264
[sniffing]

37:53.333 --> 37:55.129
[screams]

37:55.212 --> 37:57.008
Please stop this, Isabella!

38:01.224 --> 38:02.978
Izzy, stop this. This isn't you!

38:03.061 --> 38:04.607
Izzy, I know you're in there!

38:04.690 --> 38:06.736
This isn't you!

38:06.819 --> 38:08.907
I'm here. I'm Alan. I'm here. It's me.

38:08.990 --> 38:09.992
[Isabella] No!

38:10.076 --> 38:12.831
-[Mask] Yes.
-[Alan sobs]

38:18.300 --> 38:20.012
[Mask] What are you doing?

38:20.096 --> 38:22.266
[Isabella] Get off!

38:22.350 --> 38:25.272
[Mask] You were meant to be
a troll. You are weak!

38:25.356 --> 38:27.611
Get off!
[Isabella screaming, crying]

38:29.030 --> 38:31.536
Hey! I said get off!

38:33.455 --> 38:34.959
[Isabella panting]

38:38.550 --> 38:40.177
No, it's okay, it's me.

38:40.261 --> 38:41.973
I promise, it's me.

38:42.056 --> 38:43.433
I'm so sorry.

38:43.518 --> 38:44.895
[Alan sobbing]

38:44.979 --> 38:47.191
[Isabella sobs] I'm so sorry.

38:47.275 --> 38:49.362
I'm so sorry, I'm so sorry, I'm so sorry.

38:49.445 --> 38:51.449
I'm so sorry, I'm so sorry.

38:51.534 --> 38:53.036
I'm so sorry.

39:03.683 --> 39:05.311
[sighs]
Mom's never gonna buy it.

39:05.394 --> 39:06.689
A bear in the yard?

39:07.858 --> 39:09.612
I mean, if we both stick to it,

39:09.695 --> 39:11.489
she doesn't have a choice.

39:11.574 --> 39:14.538
Besides, you know
she can't resist this face.

39:14.622 --> 39:16.082
[both chuckle]

39:18.838 --> 39:20.967
[Mask hissing]

39:29.860 --> 39:31.989
Should we say
a prayer or something?

39:32.950 --> 39:34.452
Rot in hell?

39:34.536 --> 39:35.872
Rot in hell.

39:36.498 --> 39:37.751
Rot in hell.

39:38.586 --> 39:40.966
-Rot in hell.
-Rot in hell!

39:41.049 --> 39:43.554
-Rot in hell!
-Rot in hell!

39:44.138 --> 39:45.140
Rot in hell!

39:45.224 --> 39:46.894
[both scream]

39:58.125 --> 40:00.004
